turns.utt: The menu on the restaurant was so great to see.

I'm actually not too sure. I think that overall there are a lot of options that are good.

collection.dialogue_id: Bailey persuaded her friend to go to the movies with her because she didn't want to go alone.

turns.utt: So I ended up asking her out to the movies, but she thought I was hitting on her.

collection.dialogue_id: Sydney decided to take this business job because it would get her a better home loan.

turns.utt: I'm going take the business job.

It's going to get me a better home loan.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron was going to meet up with them to satisfy their needs but realized she did not have enough gas to get there.

Why? They were really counting on you turning up.
I just realized that there is not enough gas in my car to get there.

collection.dialogue_id: Robin assumed Sydney's expression was one of anger, because Sydney was yelling at the time.

turns.utt: Sydney, I think you need to calm down a bit.
What you talking about, I am not mad.
Yes I think you are because you are yelling right now and your brows are narrow.

collection.dialogue_id: Alex wipe Remy's eye with a tissue because she had been crying about the death of her friend.

What happened?
I had to give her some comfort as one of her friends died.

collection.dialogue_id: Sasha hated her neighbours dog as it barked all day and night so after going to the shop and buying poisonous slug pellets, Sasha gave the dog some pills.

What the hell did you do, Sash?
I have been warning my neighbor about leaving their stupid dog in the yard all night. It barks and barks and barks.

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse loved to play football, and after working hard training for two years, Jesse finally made the varsity team.

On great, congrats!
Thanks, I've been wanting this for such a long time now, and finally all my hard work has paid back!
Yeah, you should feel really proud
Yes, I am enjoying this moment.

collection.dialogue_id: Jan decided to watch the news today because a war broke out last night and her town was being attacked.

No I didnt.  Please inform me!
We were attacked by a group of rebels last night downtown.  Luckily are area was untouched.
How do you know this?  What can we do to stay safe?
I've been watching the news for further notice but we may have to leave town.

collection.dialogue_id: Kendall struck it rich at the mine and was able to pay their debts as a result.

If I were you, I'd officially consider myself lucky now.
I know, right? I made over $10,000 from the mine.
Incredible. Do you know what you're going to do with it?
Are you kidding? I can get myself totally out of debt now.

collection.dialogue_id: Aubrey was having a fight with Kai. Aubrey decided to ignore and not say a work to Kai for the rest of the day.

What happened between you two?
He said I didn't help on a project when he knows I was dealing with stuff at home all week.
Did you explain that to him?
Yes but he did not seem to care, he only cares about work.

collection.dialogue_id: It was Kendall's birthday so for surprise, Sydney got all Kendall's friends together to celebrate it.

turns.utt: I threw a surprise party for Kendall.
Wow how did it go?
It went great, she didn't expect a thing.
That's amazing I am glad the surprise worked.
I just hope Kendall enjoyed the celebration.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron checked Addison's fridge, but noticed that there wasn't anything to eat in it.

turns.utt: I opened up Addison's fridge to grab a beer and some grub, but there's nothing in there to drink or eat.

turns.utt: Sorry I couldn't talk when you called last night but I was in the middle of the movie and I really wanted to see the rest.
Jazmine said it was good, but she also said it's over three hours.
I know it sounds like a really long time, but the story is so good that you don't even know how long you have been watching.
So you think it was worth spending all of that time on it.
Definitely, I think it's the best movie I ever watched!

collection.dialogue_id: Jan made Riley's object. It was an unusual piece of work but very good.

turns.utt: I finally finished making that object d'art for my client Riley
Isn't that just a fancy way of saying a weird object that people want to pass off as high art.
Haha, yes, but he paid a lot of money for it so I'll call it whatever he likes.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron saw that the kitten was hungry. Cameron gave the kitten some food.

turns.utt: These kittens are homeless. Someone should after them.
You're right, Cameron. The world needs more people like you.
Hey can you bring me my pack, it has some food in it.
Food for what?
This cat hasn't eaten in months, I bet. I'm gonna give it some meat.

collection.dialogue_id: Addison worked hard and at the end of each month, gave the landlord their money for rent.

turns.utt: I had to put in twenty hours of overtime this week to make rent

collection.dialogue_id: Jordan had been through a lot of up and down in life so Jordan gave Austin a view of the future.

turns.utt: Do you know my friend Jordan?  He's a really good guy.
Yes, I know Jordan.  What makes him such a good guy to you?

Well, I was going through a really bad time and I was on drugs and about to drop out of school.  And Jordan sat me down and talked with me a lot and he really helped me see things through a different perspective.

collection.dialogue_id: Jordan paid attention in class because he wanted to pass the final exam that was coming up.

turns.utt: Don't bother me; I've got to concentrate.
Just read the note.
Quiet, I've got to pay attention to my lecture notes.
Who cares about that?
The lecturer was telling us what's on the final exam and some of us want to pass it. I'm going through the notes I made now.

collection.dialogue_id: Remy paid me back by putting change in my wallet.  Not ideal, but at least I got the money back this time.

turns.utt: I put the money right back in his wallet.
That is what he told me. He thought its strange.
But I paid him back. That's what counts.

collection.dialogue_id: Jan was new to the neighborhood and went out running one morning. Jan found new friends in the neighborhood on her run.

you are new in that neighborhood, so how did you manage to have a new friend
I went out running one morning and I met a lady

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse was going to buy them lunch but left his wallet with all his money at home.

turns.utt: I had an embarrassing moment at lunch today.
What happened?
I was going to buy my pizza lunch and when I was about to pay, I did not have my wallet.

collection.dialogue_id: Addison went to a horror movie with her friend even though she did not like them.

turns.utt: I went to see an awful horror movie today. Now I won't sleep for a week.
Why did you go if it was awful?
A friend of mine asked me to go with her so I did. It was terrible.
Did your friend like it?
Oh, yes! She was totally into it. Screaming and hiding her eyes.

collection.dialogue_id: Kendall lost their footing near the edge of the cliff, but Jordan prevented Kendall from falling.

turns.utt: I saved Kendall's life near a cliff.
Kendall is always reckless when climbing.
She lost her footing near the edge, and I had to drag her back.

collection.dialogue_id: After winning a prize in a writing competition, Carson received praise from others.

turns.utt: I can’t believe I won the writing contest.
I can, you are an amazing writer.
I don’t think I am better than over 100 other people though.
Well the judges thought so and that is all that matters.
I might enter another competition because that gave me a bit of a confidence boost.

collection.dialogue_id: Addison fixed their flat tire when they were broken down on the side of the road.

turns.utt: We broke down on the side of the road.
What happened?
We had a flat tire.

collection.dialogue_id: Austin wanted to give Sasha money for her birthday, but his wallet was empty.

turns.utt: Happy Birthday, Sasha!
Thanks, Austin. It's nice you came over on my birthday.
I actually came over to give you a birthday gift, but I seem to have left it at home.
Well, what is it? Your company is enough for me.
It was money. I'll run and get it later. I thought I had stuck it in my wallet.

collection.dialogue_id: Skylar made their own costume for Halloween and it was the best of all their friends.

turns.utt: I just won a costume contest for Halloween.
Oh, cool! Congratulations. Did you win anything?
I got some gift certificates.
What was your costume of?
I made a custom superhero costume.

collection.dialogue_id: Casey fell and hit their head, so Austin carried Casey along the way since they were very dizzy.

turns.utt: Lee is a really wonderful person and has a lot to offer the world, but I think sometimes people write him off because of his appearance.

collection.dialogue_id: Kai failed the first one hard, but she got it together and retook the practice test.

turns.utt: I bombed the first test! I got a 65.
You should ask Mrs. Jones if you can retake it.
It was just a practice test, but I thought I would do better than that.

collection.dialogue_id: Skylar was determined to win the championship race, but at the starting line they started running before the signal and were disqualified.

turns.utt: I can't believe one simple mistake and I am disqualified!
What did you do?
I started running a bit too early by accident.

collection.dialogue_id: Quinn changed the sheets two times and the sheets looked the best they have ever been.

turns.utt: I actually changed  my sheets twice in a month.
Look at you go. Are they finally clean?
You know that I have had to wash them a few times to get some of the stains to finally go away.

collection.dialogue_id: Tracy ran for his life after trying to steal money from a bank that happened to have a police officer inside.

I'm at the front. Why are you around the corner?
I stole money from the bank and I ran for my life when I saw a police officer inside.

collection.dialogue_id: As it was a gift from her beloved parents, Bailey happily accepted the house.

Everyone has already agreed to meet up in the morning and go out and look.

He went to Austin for drug money.

turns.utt: You shouldn't wait for me I have many chores to do.

Well the laundry and then go to the pharmacy.

collection.dialogue_id: Casey begged her mother for one since Casey had not had ice cream cones in a while.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron tried to work on commission as a stock broker. They made almost nothing.

turns.utt: I tried to work as a stock broker but I wasn't successful.
That's too bad. What was the pay?
I was paid in commission.

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse shared Jordan's love of birds, so they went bird watching.

turns.utt: I am so glad Jordan came with me today.
What did you guys get up to?
Jordan and I share the same love for birds, so we went bird watching.

collection.dialogue_id: By moving into an isolated cabin in the woods, Carson thought they could find peace.

Why would you want to do that?
I need some peace and I found a great isolated cabin in the woods.

collection.dialogue_id: Riley led Jordan to the door to the room where they were throwing a surprise party.

Oh I am so happy to hear that! Was it a surprise?
Yes it was and my job was to lead Jordan to the room.

how much money was it?
It had to be at least twenty thousand dollars.

I am glad you survived that situation.
If I had not have climbed the fence to escape the kidnappers, I would not be here.

Oh how come I thought we had loads left?
We did it I used a lot to pour onto the only disgusting cereal we had left in the house.

Yes but I was able to get what I need each semester so it'll take a while but I will get them all done.

You can ride with me.

Number one, there is no cheating. Number two, you cannot move backwards. Number three, the game will last exactly three rounds.

Did you need to me to go and get any of the party supplies?

Can you walk?
I can walk. I even climbed back up the tree.

I couldn't hear the instructor so I got up to move and then I got worried I'd disturb people.

I chose to move to the other side permanently because it was meant to be.

collection.dialogue_id: Quinn wasn't feeling well so he let the hosts know he wouldn't be able to attend the party.

When I left for work he was sick.
How was he when you returned home?
By the time I returned home from work he was better.

collection.dialogue_id: Kai got a check up from the doctor after finding a lump and got the all clear so when leaving the surgery Kai felt well.

You are good with spotting great deals.
It takes hard work and patience.

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse climbed the mountain and took a picture at the peak before putting the camera away.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron found out that Alex was being dishonest, so Cameron knew when Alex lied to Cameron.

I put the money away when I noticed this small line on the screen.

collection.dialogue_id: Aubrey was working on a math test. Aubrey understood the problem well so she had no issues.

I'm trying to impress a girl in my band class.

I mixed up the medicine I gave to the patient.

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse had a good laugh. It was a funny show.

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse wanted to pick out a book and selected the one that was best for you.

How come?
I went gambling and I lost everything, I lost every penny.

collection.dialogue_id: Sydney gave great manicures, Quinn had Sydney give him a manicure.

I just hate snakes ok?

It landed like 5 feet from the snake I didn't hurt it.

collection.dialogue_id: Janice won a trophy at the karate tournament. Bailey also got a trophy.

Thanks and good job on yours
Thank you, i cant believe we both won our categories
Yea our training really has started to pay off
Master Chi is a great Karate teacher

Why?
I need to return this dress to her. We went skinny dipping last night and the cops showed up. When we ran away carrying our clothes, her dress got caught on a thorn bush.

collection.dialogue_id: Alex lived in Cameron's house and was incredibly messy and loud at all times of the day and night.

They are loud and messy at all hours.

collection.dialogue_id: Tracy's hobby is woodworking. Tracy built things like baby cribs for the poor in their community.

collection.dialogue_id: While trying to get the snack out of the vending machine, Riley pushed Casey's fingers into the opening.

I'm trying to get my purchase out of the vending machine.

collection.dialogue_id: Alex bought a new watch for their friend that they loved a lot and wanted to see happy.

Thanks. I got it on sale.
Oh, it looks great. I would not have guessed you got it on sale!
Thanks. I'm excited to give it to her now.

collection.dialogue_id: The vendor told Skylar they were out of hot dogs. They bought a hamburger instead.

What where you craving?
I wanted to eat a hot dog.
But you're eating a hamburger.
Yeah, I had to take a hamburger instead, they didn’t have hot dogs anymore.

collection.dialogue_id: Bailey ate seafood every day until it made them sick, and then they never at it again.

Seafood is so good, why stop?

Too much of a good thing. How did it make you sick?
Food poisoning.

collection.dialogue_id: Casey was going out of town on a trip. Casey got their things together and organized.

turns.utt: I finally got all my stuff packed up and ready to go on my business trip.

Okay, aside from vegetables, what do you have?

I'll have the fries instead.

collection.dialogue_id: Sasha led the team astray by telling them to cheat, rather than get better with practice.

I told them to cheat rather than practice.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron wanted to find metal things on the beach. They bought a metal detector.

turns.utt: I'm tired of working this 9-5 job, I need to strike it rich somehow
Me too, well I heard that Bob just recently got rich from finding treasure at the beach
How did he do that?

collection.dialogue_id: Sydney found seashells in the sand, and organized them into a bunch of straight lines.

I organized them by species, size, colour, density, weight, apparent age, and other factors, then lining them up alphabetically.

collection.dialogue_id: Quinn took Bob aside and told him that she noticed how hard he has been working lately and appreciates his effort at his job.

turns.utt: One of the guys on my team Bob is a really good worker. I am lucky to have him under me.

collection.dialogue_id: Riley was competing in a gymnastics meet. Riley felt worse after she lost.

turns.utt: I have been feeling down recently.
Why is that?
I lost a competition in a gymnastics meet.

collection.dialogue_id: Sasha was teaching in school and asked a question. Sasha looked at Bailey and required an answer.

She gave me an answer, but it was incorrect so I gave her a detention.

collection.dialogue_id: starting on their famous perogi, Casey made the dough.

turns.utt: Earlier today we started on our famous perogi.
Oh yeah? What part of the recipe did you do?
I made the dough; I'm very good at that.

collection.dialogue_id: Sydney wanted to be a doctor so they knew that they had to work very hard in school to get the right grades to get in to university to study medicine.

turns.utt: I want to be a doctor.
That isn't easy.
I have to go a university and study hard and get good grades.

collection.dialogue_id: Carson lost his job and couldn't pay rent. He got evicted from his apartment and moved in with his parents.

turns.utt: Hey friend, how are you?
I am well how are you?
I am not well, It is a bad time for me, I lost my job and got evicted from my apartment and moved in with my parents.

collection.dialogue_id: Jan wanted to measure Addison to make some new clothes, so Jan put cloth on Addison's hips.

turns.utt: I need to measure Addison's body proportions so I can make some new garments.
How?
I'm going to put some cloth on Addison's hips so we can make her some fresh clothes.

collection.dialogue_id: Skylar bought a hammer at the store and started to build something in her new garage.

turns.utt: Hi, I just got myself a new hammer from the store
What are you building?
I have to put some shelves in my new garage.

collection.dialogue_id: Kendall made a living at it after vowing to do only what they loved for work.

turns.utt: I am finally doing what I love for my job, drawing for a cartoon show.
I am really proud of you, after so many years you finally love what you do for work.
I know, I did so many jobs that made me hate my life and I am finally doing what I want.

collection.dialogue_id: Sydney stayed home all day to finish a project instead of going out with her friends.

turns.utt: I haven't been out all day.
How come?
I was home working on this project all day instead of hanging with friends

collection.dialogue_id: Ryley had an argument with Jesse, their best friend.  Riley wrote Jesse a letter.

No! I just wrote her a letter to explain things

collection.dialogue_id: Aubrey wanted to impress Cameron's friends and decided that they would make something tasty to eat.

turns.utt: I'm going to invite Cameron's friends over to the house tomorrow night.
Oh you must be nervous! It's hard meeting your boyfriend's friends.
Yeah I really want them to like me. I'm going to make my famous Mexican quiche.

collection.dialogue_id: Taylor was celebrating his first Christmas in his new house and couldn't wait to put in a tree.

turns.utt: I can't wait to get my first tree!
Oh yeah you just got the new house.
Yeah, I have been there a while, but I can't wait to spend my first Christmas there.
Christmas is always the best.
It is my favorite holiday, my tree is going to be amazing.

collection.dialogue_id: Casey crunched the numbers, but could not find a way to pay for the cruise.

turns.utt: I think I might have to work some extra hours to be able to take the cruise

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse took their date to a bar that was known for serving the best hamburgers in town.

turns.utt: I think I might've eaten the best hamburger ever last night.
Weren't you out on a date?
Yes I was, and we went to a restaurant that served these unbelievable hamburgers.

collection.dialogue_id: Tracy missed the bus to school. Tracy asked Austin's family for a ride to school.

turns.utt: Tracy rode to school with us because she missed the school bus.
Did your mom or dad drive?
My dad drove, why?
I'm just surprised that Tracy built up the nerve to ask. You know how shy she can be.
Well she needed to get to school. It was either ride with us or walk.

collection.dialogue_id: Jan went to fly a kite, she badly wanted to be outside on the pretty spring day.

turns.utt: We were cooped up at home all week because of the rain.
It is nice outside now.
As soon as the rain stopped we went outside to fly a kite.
This sounds like great fun, it really is a pretty spring day.
We badly wanted to be outside, and kite flying was the perfect solution.

collection.dialogue_id: Addison had a lot of books to get through so he started one at a time.

turns.utt: What's the point of summer vacation if they give you reading assignments?
Yea, I've never understood that.
I had 3 books to read. So far, I read two.
That's great. Only one to go.
I know. Still so much to get through. The last book is thicker than the first two put together.

collection.dialogue_id: Kai is preforming in a concert. A member of the audience collapses. Kai stops playing.

turns.utt: A terrible thing happened today.
What happened today?
I was performing in a concert when a member of the audience collapsed.

collection.dialogue_id: Bailey learnt to swim then they worked really hard to learn all the different strokes in swimming and become expert at them.

turns.utt: I am now a swimming expert
Good! you learnt so fast!
Yea! I worked really hard to learn all the different strokes

collection.dialogue_id: Alex was the bouncer at the bar that kai went to. Alex allowed Kai to enter even though she is underage.

turns.utt: I let Kai into the bar even though she's underage.
Were you the bouncer that night?
I was when Kai walked up with her friends.  All of her friends are of age.

collection.dialogue_id: Casey used the money to obtain groceries instead of paying for the drugs like she was told.

turns.utt: I made a tough decision yesterday.
What was the decision?
I used the money to get groceries instead of paying for drugs.

collection.dialogue_id: Aubrey knew that Riley had betrayed her. She deliberately filled Riley's tank with pure oxygen instead of the usual nonlethal mixture.

turns.utt: I just found out that Riley betrayed me.

I will fill her tank with pure oxygen instead of the usual safe formulation.

collection.dialogue_id: Bailey had been living out west for a few years and he still got homesick often, so he called his sibling back home.

turns.utt: How is everything on the east coast?
The weather has been beautiful here. How's is it on the west coast?
I miss everyone there. It's been years.

collection.dialogue_id: Quinn texted their husband that night. They were going to be late for dinner.

turns.utt: I texted my husband today because he was supposed to be home two hours ago.  He was running late for dinner.

collection.dialogue_id: Carson and Cameron were playing pranks on each other, so Carson filled Cameron's shoes with dirt.

I know, but I was playing pranks with Cameron, and I filled Cameron's shoes with dirt as a joke. He tracked dirt everywhere all over the floor.

collection.dialogue_id: Riley saw how hard Sasha was training, so she thought Sasha would win the competition.

turns.utt: Sasha has been training extra hard for the competition.
She is has been going to the gym everyday after work.
I know that she is going to win the competition, with all that extra time she is putting in.

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse often used shopping to lessen stress so she went to the mall and bought a new outfit after she lost out on a promotion.

turns.utt: I can't believe that I didn't get the promotion.
Maybe we should go to the mall?
Shopping always helps me cope with stress.
I love to go shopping.
I love the new outfit I found at the mall.

collection.dialogue_id: Taylor was best friends with her childhood neighbor and after years of being such good friends, Taylor married the neighbor.

Well, he used to be my neighbour when we were kids.
No kidding! You've known him for all these years?
Yeah, we were best friends growing up and ended up getting married after all these years!

collection.dialogue_id: Jan had broken both their arms but was thirsty, so Addison filled Jan's mouth with water.

turns.utt: I had to hand feed Jan her water today.
Why can't she drink it herself?
She broke both arms and can't even lift a cup yet.

collection.dialogue_id: Bailey tipped the scales with her weight and was given a stern warning about her health.

turns.utt: I had a doctor's appointment today.

Everything went well. However, my weight was a little higher than my expectations.

collection.dialogue_id: Casey worked at a barber shop to cut people's hair. Casey cut Quinn's hair.

turns.utt: Casey thanks for cutting my hair today, I didn't even realize you worked here

collection.dialogue_id: Skylar got worse at math. If such a thing is even possible.

turns.utt: I'm just really struggling with math.
We all have subjects at school we're not good at.
Yeah, but it seems like I'm getting worse at it, if that's possible.

collection.dialogue_id: Bailey placed Taylor at the head of the class because Taylor is a responsible person with a good grade.

turns.utt: Bailey assigned me as the class head today.
That's exciting, I knew she would, you're the mot responsible person in class.
Thanks, I kind knew she would too.

collection.dialogue_id: Bailey supplied the school with food, and made sure the kids had healthy alternatives to the usual junk.

I thought they were paying you to work there?
Well, I like to bring the kids fruits to have healthy snacks.

collection.dialogue_id: After cooking, Taylor liked to clean up the kitchen and throw away any trash.

turns.utt: I just finished cleaning up my kitchen and getting the trash out.
I don't envy you. I hate cleaning.
I'm the other way. I love cleaning, and then seeing my nice clean kitchen afterwards.

Well after our movie date, we ate dinner and we really had a great time.

But maybe he should change his approach. Yelling at people makes you look crazy!!

collection.dialogue_id: Casey got the friends together.  They planned to go for a picnic.

turns.utt: We're all went out for a nice picnic lunch earlier.

To the park, the place by the lake.

I've been taking self-paced courses online, reading books, and practicing real-world skills as well.

I raked the coals and I got it started up.

Mark. I was nervous I couldn't make new friends.

I can contact everyone first and then pick.

All my colleagues think I'm an underdog, but my clients are all satisfied.

Yes you really got lucky there, but most new items have some kind of warranty

I never got how people can talk about true love but then put timetables on when to do things.

Hmm sounds like there was already trouble in paradise
I wish I had known he had never kissed a girl before I went in for that kiss!

Cheerios are easily better that Coco Puffs.
Huh?  It was about something that stupid?
How is cereal stupid?

Well, I almost fell as the crowd watched but luckily I spun off and caught myself.

I did already. I had to hold my emotions until it came to an end.

As a dentist you have probably seen it all. But sounds like this was extraordinary.
It was. This person had anomalous teeth, something I haven't encountered much. I ended up saving his teeth.

collection.dialogue_id: Kai wanted to drive home in the middle of the snowstorm, but Sydney wanted Kai to stay.

turns.utt: I really needed to get back home yesterday, but there was a terrible snowstorm.

collection.dialogue_id: Jesse recently bought an e-book reader. Jesse liked to read.

turns.utt: You know I like to read right? I finally got myself an e-book reader.

I couldn't stop the words from rolling off of my tongue though. I was just so upset that she wasn't listening to my point of view.

collection.dialogue_id: Kai has to give a presentation in their class but Kai was not prepared.  Therefore, Kai makes things up as they go along.

It was. There was this antique looking item that I had to take get checked out.

collection.dialogue_id: Carson seemed like they wanted to focus on work. Kai left Carson alone.

turns.utt: Carson was ignoring me all day. He was really into his work.
Why did you stay there then?
I didn't. I left so he could focus, but I was really hoping to hang out with him.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron gave the class their snacks. They were hungry and looked happy to be receiving the food.

turns.utt: The class was so happy when I gave them those snacks. They were hungry because they were out running around all morning.

collection.dialogue_id: Alex was failing her paper and asked Addison for help. Addison gave Alex assurance.

turns.utt: Did I tell you what Addison did for me the other day?
No what did she do?
I was failing my paper and she offered to help.

collection.dialogue_id: Skylar was expecting to see Addison's first child, but Addison refused to show Skylar their child.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron was helping Jan move to another residence. Cameron moved Jan's furniture.

turns.utt: I'm shattered after yesterday.
What were you doing?.
I was helping Jan move house, she has a lot of stuff!.

We need to do an onside kick because we can't stop them from scoring at all.

collection.dialogue_id: After finding a way to the store, Cameron bought a lot of food and felt like a champion.

turns.utt: I had to ask my neighbor to give me a ride to the store because my car is broken down.

collection.dialogue_id: Jordan took to cooking like a duck to water and graduated cooking school at the top of her class.

turns.utt: I finally graduated cooking school.
Congratulations! I know how good you were at cooking ..
It was pretty easy. And I graduated at the top of my class .

collection.dialogue_id: Sasha picked the pink dress and after trying it on, she bought it at the store and brought it home.

turns.utt: I wanted to get a new dress.
It is about time.
I picked out the pink one and after trying it on, I fell in love with it.
Did you buy it?
I bought it right away at the store and brought it home.

collection.dialogue_id: The post office was busy, so Skylar helped forward the mail.

turns.utt: Hey how are you doing?

I did see a lot of cars outside the post office when I pulled up.

collection.dialogue_id: Casey took Austin chances, rolled the dice, it hit seven, and won a lot of money.

collection.dialogue_id: Jan wanted to raise money for her school so she went door to door selling brownies.

turns.utt: I am so tired.
Why?
I've been going door to door selling brownies since 7 in the morning.

collection.dialogue_id: Quinn asked Austin to describe the painting since the picture he sent of it was not very clear.

Why do you say that?
Because he sent me a picture of the painting, but the quality wasn't that clear on the picture.

collection.dialogue_id: Cameron would make fun of Austin when he spoke in front of their coworkers at workplace.

He's a jerk. Every time it's his turn to talk at work, he tries to make fun of me, in some way.

collection.dialogue_id: Taylor's math test was that afternoon at school. Taylor tried very hard to pass it.

Well, I studied very hard, but it was much more difficult than I had thought.

collection.dialogue_id: Skylar ignored Remy's mother by running off to the toy section of the store and was grounded as a result.

turns.utt: I was grounded.
What did you do?
I ran to the toy section when Remy's mom told me not to.

collection.dialogue_id: Addison checked Skylar's car for her phone but was unable to find it even after cleaning everything.

turns.utt: I just don' t know where I put the phone.
Did you check Skylar' s car?
I checked everywhere for it.

collection.dialogue_id: Sasha had gotten a tutor to help her with history. Sasha started to improve slowly.

turns.utt: This tutor has helped so much!
